      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SCOTT ELYSIAN (8) is having her first start around this course. Comes here after a last start 4th and beaten 7 lengths (23.75) at The Gardens. Good beginner but will need a little luck early crossing from an outside draw. Should bounce back. MAURITIAN NITRO (4) pinged the lids and was in the firing line throughout but drifted out of it when 6th at this track in a Grade 5. The form from his last run is stacking up nicely. Key runner who gets his chance to atone. ALBATROSS (1) has been hard to follow lately, running eighth (20.36) last time but prior to that ran very well when placed at Richmond. Safe beginner and drawn well on the inside. Can find the frame this time. QUEEN JEWEL (5) looks an each-way chance.",
